4534 // eventually disable vectorization.
4535 BundleMember->Dependencies++;
4536 BundleMember->incrementUnscheduledDeps(1);
4537 }
4538 }
4539 }
4540
4541 // Handle the memory dependencies.
4542 ScheduleData *DepDest = BundleMember->NextLoadStore;
4543 if (DepDest) {
4544 Instruction *SrcInst = BundleMember->Inst;
4545 MemoryLocation SrcLoc = getLocation(SrcInst, SLP->AA);
4546 bool SrcMayWrite = BundleMember->Inst->mayWriteToMemory();
4547 unsigned numAliased = 0;
4548 unsigned DistToSrc = 1;
4549
4550 while (DepDest) {
4551 assert(isInSchedulingRegion(DepDest));
4552
4553 // We have two limits to reduce the complexity:
4554 // 1) AliasedCheckLimit: It's a small limit to reduce calls to
4555 // SLP->isAliased (which is the expensive part in this loop).
4556 // 2) MaxMemDepDistance: It's for very large blocks and it aborts
4557 // the whole loop (even if the loop is fast, it's quadratic).
4558 // It's important for the loop break condition (see below) to
4559 // check this limit even between two read-only instructions.
4560 if (DistToSrc >= MaxMemDepDistance ||
4561 ((SrcMayWrite || DepDest->Inst->mayWriteToMemory()) &&
4562 (numAliased >= AliasedCheckLimit ||
4563 SLP->isAliased(SrcLoc, SrcInst, DepDest->Inst)))) {
4564
4565 // We increment the counter only if the locations are aliased
4566 // (instead of counting all alias checks). This gives a better
4567 // balance between reduced runtime and accurate dependencies.
4568 numAliased++;
4569
4570 DepDest->MemoryDependencies.push_back(BundleMember);
4571 BundleMember->Dependencies++;
4572 ScheduleData *DestBundle = DepDest->FirstInBundle;
4573 if (!DestBundle->IsScheduled) {
4574 BundleMember->incrementUnscheduledDeps(1);
4575 }
4576 if (!DestBundle->hasValidDependencies()) {
4577 WorkList.push_back(DestBundle);
4578 }
4579 }
4580 DepDest = DepDest->NextLoadStore;
4581
4582 // Example, explaining the loop break condition: Let's assume our
4583 // starting instruction is i0 and MaxMemDepDistance = 3.
4584 //
4585 // +--------v--v--v
4586 // i0,i1,i2,i3,i4,i5,i6,i7,i8
4587 // +--------^--^--^
4588 //
4589 // MaxMemDepDistance let us stop alias-checking at i3 and we add
4590 // dependencies from i0 to i3,i4,.. (even if they are not aliased).
4591 // Previously we already added dependencies from i3 to i6,i7,i8
4592 // (because of MaxMemDepDistance). As we added a dependency from
4593 // i0 to i3, we have transitive dependencies from i0 to i6,i7,i8
4594 // and we can abort this loop at i6.
4595 if (DistToSrc >= 2 * MaxMemDepDistance)
4596 break;
4597 DistToSrc++;
4598 }
4599 }
4600 }
4601 BundleMember = BundleMember->NextInBundle;
4602 }
4603 if (InsertInReadyList && SD->isReady()) {
4604 ReadyInsts.push_back(SD);
4605 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: gets ready on update: " << *SD->Inst
4606 << "\n");
4607 }
4608 }
4609}
4610
4611void BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::resetSchedule() {
4612 assert(ScheduleStart &&
4613 "tried to reset schedule on block which has not been scheduled");
4614 for (Instruction *I = ScheduleStart; I != ScheduleEnd; I = I->getNextNode()) {
4615 doForAllOpcodes(I, [&](ScheduleData *SD) {
4616 assert(isInSchedulingRegion(SD) &&
4617 "ScheduleData not in scheduling region");
4618 SD->IsScheduled = false;
4619 SD->resetUnscheduledDeps();
4620 });
4621 }
4622 ReadyInsts.clear();
4623}
4624
4625void BoUpSLP::scheduleBlock(BlockScheduling *BS) {
4626 if (!BS->ScheduleStart)
4627 return;
4628
4629 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: schedule block " << BS->BB->getName() << "\n");
4630
4631 BS->resetSchedule();
4632
4633 // For the real scheduling we use a more sophisticated ready-list: it is
4634 // sorted by the original instruction location. This lets the final schedule
4635 // be as close as possible to the original instruction order.
4636 struct ScheduleDataCompare {
4637 bool operator()(ScheduleData *SD1, ScheduleData *SD2) const {
4638 return SD2->SchedulingPriority < SD1->SchedulingPriority;
4639 }
4640 };
4641 std::set<ScheduleData *, ScheduleDataCompare> ReadyInsts;
4642
4643 // Ensure that all dependency data is updated and fill the ready-list with
4644 // initial instructions.
4645 int Idx = 0;
4646 int NumToSchedule = 0;
4647 for (auto *I = BS->ScheduleStart; I != BS->ScheduleEnd;
4648 I = I->getNextNode()) {
4649 BS->doForAllOpcodes(I, [this, &Idx, &NumToSchedule, BS](ScheduleData *SD) {
4650 assert(SD->isPartOfBundle() ==
4651 (getTreeEntry(SD->Inst) != nullptr) &&
4652 "scheduler and vectorizer bundle mismatch");
4653 SD->FirstInBundle->SchedulingPriority = Idx++;
4654 if (SD->isSchedulingEntity()) {
4655 BS->calculateDependencies(SD, false, this);
4656 NumToSchedule++;
4657 }
4658 });
4659 }
4660 BS->initialFillReadyList(ReadyInsts);
4661
4662 Instruction *LastScheduledInst = BS->ScheduleEnd;
4663
4664 // Do the "real" scheduling.
4665 while (!ReadyInsts.empty()) {
4666 ScheduleData *picked = *ReadyInsts.begin();
4667 ReadyInsts.erase(ReadyInsts.begin());
4668
4669 // Move the scheduled instruction(s) to their dedicated places, if not
4670 // there yet.
4671 ScheduleData *BundleMember = picked;
4672 while (BundleMember) {
4673 Instruction *pickedInst = BundleMember->Inst;
4674 if (LastScheduledInst->getNextNode() != pickedInst) {
4675 BS->BB->getInstList().remove(pickedInst);
4676 BS->BB->getInstList().insert(LastScheduledInst->getIterator(),
4677 pickedInst);
4678 }
4679 LastScheduledInst = pickedInst;
4680 BundleMember = BundleMember->NextInBundle;
4681 }
4682
4683 BS->schedule(picked, ReadyInsts);
4684 NumToSchedule--;
4685 }
4686 assert(NumToSchedule == 0 && "could not schedule all instructions");
4687
4688 // Avoid duplicate scheduling of the block.
4689 BS->ScheduleStart = nullptr;
4690}
4691
4692unsigned BoUpSLP::getVectorElementSize(Value *V) const {
4693 // If V is a store, just return the width of the stored value without
4694 // traversing the expression tree. This is the common case.
4695 if (auto *Store = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(V))
4696 return DL->getTypeSizeInBits(Store->getValueOperand()->getType());
4697
4698 // If V is not a store, we can traverse the expression tree to find loads
4699 // that feed it. The type of the loaded value may indicate a more suitable
4700 // width than V's type. We want to base the vector element size on the width
4701 // of memory operations where possible.
4702 SmallVector<Instruction *, 16> Worklist;
4703 SmallPtrSet<Instruction *, 16> Visited;
4704 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V))
4705 Worklist.push_back(I);
4706
4707 // Traverse the expression tree in bottom-up order looking for loads. If we
4708 // encounter an instruction we don't yet handle, we give up.
4709 auto MaxWidth = 0u;
4710 auto FoundUnknownInst = false;
4711 while (!Worklist.empty() && !FoundUnknownInst) {
4712 auto *I = Worklist.pop_back_val();
4713 Visited.insert(I);
4714
4715 // We should only be looking at scalar instructions here. If the current
4716 // instruction has a vector type, give up.
4717 auto *Ty = I->getType();
4718 if (isa<VectorType>(Ty))
4719 FoundUnknownInst = true;
4720
4721 // If the current instruction is a load, update MaxWidth to reflect the
4722 // width of the loaded value.
4723 else if (isa<LoadInst>(I))
4724 MaxWidth = std::max<unsigned>(MaxWidth, DL->getTypeSizeInBits(Ty));
4725
4726 // Otherwise, we need to visit the operands of the instruction. We only
4727 // handle the interesting cases from buildTree here. If an operand is an
4728 // instruction we haven't yet visited, we add it to the worklist.
4729 else if (isa<PHINode>(I) || isa<CastInst>(I) || isa<GetElementPtrInst>(I) ||
4730 isa<CmpInst>(I) || isa<SelectInst>(I) || isa<BinaryOperator>(I)) {
4731 for (Use &U : I->operands())
4732 if (auto *J = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U.get()))
4733 if (!Visited.count(J))
4734 Worklist.push_back(J);
4735 }
4736
4737 // If we don't yet handle the instruction, give up.
4738 else
4739 FoundUnknownInst = true;
4740 }
4741
4742 // If we didn't encounter a memory access in the expression tree, or if we
4743 // gave up for some reason, just return the width of V.
4744 if (!MaxWidth || FoundUnknownInst)
4745 return DL->getTypeSizeInBits(V->getType());
4746
4747 // Otherwise, return the maximum width we found.
4748 return MaxWidth;
4749}
4750
4751// Determine if a value V in a vectorizable expression Expr can be demoted to a
4752// smaller type with a truncation. We collect the values that will be demoted
4753// in ToDemote and additional roots that require investigating in Roots.
4754static bool collectValuesToDemote(Value *V, SmallPtrSetImpl<Value *> &Expr,
4755 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &ToDemote,
4756 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &Roots) {
4757 // We can always demote constants.
4758 if (isa<Constant>(V)) {
4759 ToDemote.push_back(V);
4760 return true;
4761 }
4762
4763 // If the value is not an instruction in the expression with only one use, it
4764 // cannot be demoted.
4765 auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
4766 if (!I || !I->hasOneUse() || !Expr.count(I))
4767 return false;
4768
4769 switch (I->getOpcode()) {
4770
4771 // We can always demote truncations and extensions. Since truncations can
4772 // seed additional demotion, we save the truncated value.
4773 case Instruction::Trunc:
4774 Roots.push_back(I->getOperand(0));
4775 break;
4776 case Instruction::ZExt:
4777 case Instruction::SExt:
4778 break;
4779
4780 // We can demote certain binary operations if we can demote both of their
4781 // operands.
4782 case Instruction::Add:
4783 case Instruction::Sub:
4784 case Instruction::Mul:
4785 case Instruction::And:
4786 case Instruction::Or:
4787 case Instruction::Xor:
4788 if (!collectValuesToDemote(I->getOperand(0), Expr, ToDemote, Roots) ||
4789 !collectValuesToDemote(I->getOperand(1), Expr, ToDemote, Roots))
4790 return false;
4791 break;
4792
4793 // We can demote selects if we can demote their true and false values.
4794 case Instruction::Select: {
4795 SelectInst *SI = cast<SelectInst>(I);
4796 if (!collectValuesToDemote(SI->getTrueValue(), Expr, ToDemote, Roots) ||
4797 !collectValuesToDemote(SI->getFalseValue(), Expr, ToDemote, Roots))
4798 return false;
4799 break;
4800 }
4801
4802 // We can demote phis if we can demote all their incoming operands. Note that
4803 // we don't need to worry about cycles since we ensure single use above.
4804 case Instruction::PHI: {
4805 PHINode *PN = cast<PHINode>(I);
4806 for (Value *IncValue : PN->incoming_values())
4807 if (!collectValuesToDemote(IncValue, Expr, ToDemote, Roots))
4808 return false;
4809 break;
4810 }
4811
4812 // Otherwise, conservatively give up.
4813 default:
4814 return false;
4815 }
4816
4817 // Record the value that we can demote.
4818 ToDemote.push_back(V);
4819 return true;
4820}
4821
4822void BoUpSLP::computeMinimumValueSizes() {
4823 // If there are no external uses, the expression tree must be rooted by a
4824 // store. We can't demote in-memory values, so there is nothing to do here.
4825 if (ExternalUses.empty())
4826 return;
4827
4828 // We only attempt to truncate integer expressions.
4829 auto &TreeRoot = VectorizableTree[0]->Scalars;
4830 auto *TreeRootIT = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(TreeRoot[0]->getType());
4831 if (!TreeRootIT)
4832 return;
4833
4834 // If the expression is not rooted by a store, these roots should have
4835 // external uses. We will rely on InstCombine to rewrite the expression in
4836 // the narrower type. However, InstCombine only rewrites single-use values.
4837 // This means that if a tree entry other than a root is used externally, it
4838 // must have multiple uses and InstCombine will not rewrite it. The code
4839 // below ensures that only the roots are used externally.
4840 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 32> Expr(TreeRoot.begin(), TreeRoot.end());
4841 for (auto &EU : ExternalUses)
4842 if (!Expr.erase(EU.Scalar))
4843 return;
4844 if (!Expr.empty())
4845 return;
4846
4847 // Collect the scalar values of the vectorizable expression. We will use this
4848 // context to determine which values can be demoted. If we see a truncation,
4849 // we mark it as seeding another demotion.
4850 for (auto &EntryPtr : VectorizableTree)
4851 Expr.insert(EntryPtr->Scalars.begin(), EntryPtr->Scalars.end());
4852
4853 // Ensure the roots of the vectorizable tree don't form a cycle. They must
4854 // have a single external user that is not in the vectorizable tree.
4855 for (auto *Root : TreeRoot)
4856 if (!Root->hasOneUse() || Expr.count(*Root->user_begin()))
4857 return;
4858
4859 // Conservatively determine if we can actually truncate the roots of the
4860 // expression. Collect the values that can be demoted in ToDemote and
4861 // additional roots that require investigating in Roots.
4862 SmallVector<Value *, 32> ToDemote;
4863 SmallVector<Value *, 4> Roots;
4864 for (auto *Root : TreeRoot)
4865 if (!collectValuesToDemote(Root, Expr, ToDemote, Roots))
4866 return;
4867
4868 // The maximum bit width required to represent all the values that can be
4869 // demoted without loss of precision. It would be safe to truncate the roots
4870 // of the expression to this width.
4871 auto MaxBitWidth = 8u;
4872
4873 // We first check if all the bits of the roots are demanded. If they're not,
4874 // we can truncate the roots to this narrower type.
4875 for (auto *Root : TreeRoot) {
4876 auto Mask = DB->getDemandedBits(cast<Instruction>(Root));
4877 MaxBitWidth = std::max<unsigned>(
4878 Mask.getBitWidth() - Mask.countLeadingZeros(), MaxBitWidth);
4879 }
4880
4881 // True if the roots can be zero-extended back to their original type, rather
4882 // than sign-extended. We know that if the leading bits are not demanded, we
4883 // can safely zero-extend. So we initialize IsKnownPositive to True.
4884 bool IsKnownPositive = true;
4885
4886 // If all the bits of the roots are demanded, we can try a little harder to
4887 // compute a narrower type. This can happen, for example, if the roots are
4888 // getelementptr indices. InstCombine promotes these indices to the pointer
4889 // width. Thus, all their bits are technically demanded even though the
4890 // address computation might be vectorized in a smaller type.
4891 //
4892 // We start by looking at each entry that can be demoted. We compute the
4893 // maximum bit width required to store the scalar by using ValueTracking to
4894 // compute the number of high-order bits we can truncate.
4895 if (MaxBitWidth == DL->getTypeSizeInBits(TreeRoot[0]->getType()) &&
4896 llvm::all_of(TreeRoot, [](Value *R) {
4897 assert(R->hasOneUse() && "Root should have only one use!");
4898 return isa<GetElementPtrInst>(R->user_back());
4899 })) {
4900 MaxBitWidth = 8u;
4901
4902 // Determine if the sign bit of all the roots is known to be zero. If not,
4903 // IsKnownPositive is set to False.
4904 IsKnownPositive = llvm::all_of(TreeRoot, [&](Value *R) {
4905 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(R, *DL);
4906 return Known.isNonNegative();
4907 });
4908
4909 // Determine the maximum number of bits required to store the scalar
4910 // values.
4911 for (auto *Scalar : ToDemote) {
4912 auto NumSignBits = ComputeNumSignBits(Scalar, *DL, 0, AC, nullptr, DT);
4913 auto NumTypeBits = DL->getTypeSizeInBits(Scalar->getType());
4914 MaxBitWidth = std::max<unsigned>(NumTypeBits - NumSignBits, MaxBitWidth);
4915 }
4916
4917 // If we can't prove that the sign bit is zero, we must add one to the
4918 // maximum bit width to account for the unknown sign bit. This preserves
4919 // the existing sign bit so we can safely sign-extend the root back to the
4920 // original type. Otherwise, if we know the sign bit is zero, we will
4921 // zero-extend the root instead.
4922 //
4923 // FIXME: This is somewhat suboptimal, as there will be cases where adding
4924 // one to the maximum bit width will yield a larger-than-necessary
4925 // type. In general, we need to add an extra bit only if we can't
4926 // prove that the upper bit of the original type is equal to the
4927 // upper bit of the proposed smaller type. If these two bits are the
4928 // same (either zero or one) we know that sign-extending from the
4929 // smaller type will result in the same value. Here, since we can't
4930 // yet prove this, we are just making the proposed smaller type
4931 // larger to ensure correctness.
4932 if (!IsKnownPositive)
4933 ++MaxBitWidth;
4934 }
4935
4936 // Round MaxBitWidth up to the next power-of-two.
4937 if (!isPowerOf2_64(MaxBitWidth))
4938 MaxBitWidth = NextPowerOf2(MaxBitWidth);
4939
4940 // If the maximum bit width we compute is less than the with of the roots'
4941 // type, we can proceed with the narrowing. Otherwise, do nothing.
4942 if (MaxBitWidth >= TreeRootIT->getBitWidth())
4943 return;
4944
4945 // If we can truncate the root, we must collect additional values that might
4946 // be demoted as a result. That is, those seeded by truncations we will
4947 // modify.
4948 while (!Roots.empty())
4949 collectValuesToDemote(Roots.pop_back_val(), Expr, ToDemote, Roots);
4950
4951 // Finally, map the values we can demote to the maximum bit with we computed.
4952 for (auto *Scalar : ToDemote)
4953 MinBWs[Scalar] = std::make_pair(MaxBitWidth, !IsKnownPositive);
4954}
4955
4956namespace {
4957
4958/// The SLPVectorizer Pass.
4959struct SLPVectorizer : public FunctionPass {
4960 SLPVectorizerPass Impl;
4961
4962 /// Pass identification, replacement for typeid
4963 static char ID;
4964
4965 explicit SLPVectorizer() : FunctionPass(ID) {
4966 initializeSLPVectorizerPass(*PassRegistry::getPassRegistry());
4967 }
4968
4969 bool doInitialization(Module &M) override {
4970 return false;
4971 }
4972
4973 bool runOnFunction(Function &F) override {
4974 if (skipFunction(F))
4975 return false;
4976
4977 auto *SE = &getAnalysis<ScalarEvolutionWrapperPass>().getSE();
4978 auto *TTI = &getAnalysis<TargetTransformInfoWrapperPass>().getTTI(F);
4979 auto *TLIP = getAnalysisIfAvailable<TargetLibraryInfoWrapperPass>();
4980 auto *TLI = TLIP ? &TLIP->getTLI() : nullptr;
4981 auto *AA = &getAnalysis<AAResultsWrapperPass>().getAAResults();
4982 auto *LI = &getAnalysis<LoopInfoWrapperPass>().getLoopInfo();
4983 auto *DT = &getAnalysis<DominatorTreeWrapperPass>().getDomTree();
4984 auto *AC = &getAnalysis<AssumptionCacheTracker>().getAssumptionCache(F);
4985 auto *DB = &getAnalysis<DemandedBitsWrapperPass>().getDemandedBits();
4986 auto *ORE = &getAnalysis<OptimizationRemarkEmitterWrapperPass>().getORE();
4987
4988 return Impl.runImpl(F, SE, TTI, TLI, AA, LI, DT, AC, DB, ORE);
4989 }
4990
4991 void getAnalysisUsage(AnalysisUsage &AU) const override {
4992 FunctionPass::getAnalysisUsage(AU);
4993 AU.addRequired<AssumptionCacheTracker>();
4994 AU.addRequired<ScalarEvolutionWrapperPass>();
4995 AU.addRequired<AAResultsWrapperPass>();
4996 AU.addRequired<TargetTransformInfoWrapperPass>();
4997 AU.addRequired<LoopInfoWrapperPass>();
4998 AU.addRequired<DominatorTreeWrapperPass>();
4999 AU.addRequired<DemandedBitsWrapperPass>();
5000 AU.addRequired<OptimizationRemarkEmitterWrapperPass>();
5001 AU.addPreserved<LoopInfoWrapperPass>();
5002 AU.addPreserved<DominatorTreeWrapperPass>();
5003 AU.addPreserved<AAResultsWrapperPass>();
5004 AU.addPreserved<GlobalsAAWrapperPass>();
5005 AU.setPreservesCFG();
5006 }
5007};
5008
5009} // end anonymous namespace
5010
5011PreservedAnalyses SLPVectorizerPass::run(Function &F, FunctionAnalysisManager &AM) {
5012 auto *SE = &AM.getResult<ScalarEvolutionAnalysis>(F);
5013 auto *TTI = &AM.getResult<TargetIRAnalysis>(F);
5014 auto *TLI = AM.getCachedResult<TargetLibraryAnalysis>(F);
5015 auto *AA = &AM.getResult<AAManager>(F);
5016 auto *LI = &AM.getResult<LoopAnalysis>(F);
5017 auto *DT = &AM.getResult<DominatorTreeAnalysis>(F);
5018 auto *AC = &AM.getResult<AssumptionAnalysis>(F);
5019 auto *DB = &AM.getResult<DemandedBitsAnalysis>(F);
5020 auto *ORE = &AM.getResult<OptimizationRemarkEmitterAnalysis>(F);
5021
5022 bool Changed = runImpl(F, SE, TTI, TLI, AA, LI, DT, AC, DB, ORE);
5023 if (!Changed)
5024 return PreservedAnalyses::all();
5025
5026 PreservedAnalyses PA;
5027 PA.preserveSet<CFGAnalyses>();
5028 PA.preserve<AAManager>();
5029 PA.preserve<GlobalsAA>();
5030 return PA;
5031}
5032
5033bool SLPVectorizerPass::runImpl(Function &F, ScalarEvolution *SE_,
5034 TargetTransformInfo *TTI_,
5035 TargetLibraryInfo *TLI_, AliasAnalysis *AA_,
5036 LoopInfo *LI_, DominatorTree *DT_,
5037 AssumptionCache *AC_, DemandedBits *DB_,
5038 OptimizationRemarkEmitter *ORE_) {
5039 SE = SE_;
5040 TTI = TTI_;
5041 TLI = TLI_;
5042 AA = AA_;
5043 LI = LI_;
5044 DT = DT_;
5045 AC = AC_;
5046 DB = DB_;
5047 DL = &F.getParent()->getDataLayout();
5048
5049 Stores.clear();
5050 GEPs.clear();
5051 bool Changed = false;
5052
5053 // If the target claims to have no vector registers don't attempt
5054 // vectorization.
5055 if (!TTI->getNumberOfRegisters(true))
5056 return false;
5057
5058 // Don't vectorize when the attribute NoImplicitFloat is used.
5059 if (F.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::NoImplicitFloat))
5060 return false;
5061
5062 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Analyzing blocks in " << F.getName() << ".\n");
5063
5064 // Use the bottom up slp vectorizer to construct chains that start with
5065 // store instructions.
5066 BoUpSLP R(&F, SE, TTI, TLI, AA, LI, DT, AC, DB, DL, ORE_);
5067
5068 // A general note: the vectorizer must use BoUpSLP::eraseInstruction() to
5069 // delete instructions.
5070
5071 // Scan the blocks in the function in post order.
5072 for (auto BB : post_order(&F.getEntryBlock())) {
5073 collectSeedInstructions(BB);
5074
5075 // Vectorize trees that end at stores.
5076 if (!Stores.empty()) {
5077 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Found stores for " << Stores.size()
5078 << " underlying objects.\n");
5079 Changed |= vectorizeStoreChains(R);
5080 }
5081
5082 // Vectorize trees that end at reductions.
5083 Changed |= vectorizeChainsInBlock(BB, R);
5084
5085 // Vectorize the index computations of getelementptr instructions. This
5086 // is primarily intended to catch gather-like idioms ending at
5087 // non-consecutive loads.
5088 if (!GEPs.empty()) {
5089 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Found GEPs for " << GEPs.size()
5090 << " underlying objects.\n");
5091 Changed |= vectorizeGEPIndices(BB, R);
5092 }
5093 }
5094
5095 if (Changed) {
5096 R.optimizeGatherSequence();
5097 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: vectorized \"" << F.getName() << "\"\n");
5098 LLVM_DEBUG(verifyFunction(F));
5099 }
5100 return Changed;
5101}
5102
5103/// Check that the Values in the slice in VL array are still existent in
5104/// the WeakTrackingVH array.
5105/// Vectorization of part of the VL array may cause later values in the VL array
5106/// to become invalid. We track when this has happened in the WeakTrackingVH
5107/// array.
5108static bool hasValueBeenRAUWed(ArrayRef<Value *> VL,
5109 ArrayRef<WeakTrackingVH> VH, unsigned SliceBegin,
5110 unsigned SliceSize) {
5111 VL = VL.slice(SliceBegin, SliceSize);
5112 VH = VH.slice(SliceBegin, SliceSize);
5113 return !std::equal(VL.begin(), VL.end(), VH.begin());
5114}
5115
5116bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeStoreChain(ArrayRef<Value *> Chain, BoUpSLP &R,
5117 unsigned VecRegSize) {
5118 const unsigned ChainLen = Chain.size();
5119 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Analyzing a store chain of length " << ChainLen
5120 << "\n");
5121 const unsigned Sz = R.getVectorElementSize(Chain[0]);
5122 const unsigned VF = VecRegSize / Sz;
5123
5124 if (!isPowerOf2_32(Sz) || VF < 2)
5125 return false;
5126
5127 // Keep track of values that were deleted by vectorizing in the loop below.
5128 const SmallVector<WeakTrackingVH, 8> TrackValues(Chain.begin(), Chain.end());
5129
5130 bool Changed = false;
5131 // Look for profitable vectorizable trees at all offsets, starting at zero.
5132 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ChainLen; i + VF <= e; ++i) {
5133
5134 // Check that a previous iteration of this loop did not delete the Value.
5135 if (hasValueBeenRAUWed(Chain, TrackValues, i, VF))
5136 continue;
5137
5138 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Analyzing " << VF << " stores at offset " << i
5139 << "\n");
5140 ArrayRef<Value *> Operands = Chain.slice(i, VF);
5141
5142 R.buildTree(Operands);
5143 if (R.isTreeTinyAndNotFullyVectorizable())
5144 continue;
5145
5146 R.computeMinimumValueSizes();
5147
5148 int Cost = R.getTreeCost();
5149
5150 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Found cost=" << Cost << " for VF=" << VF
5151 << "\n");
5152 if (Cost < -SLPCostThreshold) {
5153 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Decided to vectorize cost=" << Cost << "\n");
5154
5155 using namespace ore;
5156
5157 R.getORE()->emit(OptimizationRemark(SV_NAME, "StoresVectorized",
5158 cast<StoreInst>(Chain[i]))
5159 << "Stores SLP vectorized with cost " << NV("Cost", Cost)
5160 << " and with tree size "
5161 << NV("TreeSize", R.getTreeSize()));
5162
5163 R.vectorizeTree();
5164
5165 // Move to the next bundle.
5166 i += VF - 1;
5167 Changed = true;
5168 }
5169 }
5170
5171 return Changed;
5172}
5173
5174bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeStores(ArrayRef<StoreInst *> Stores,
5175 BoUpSLP &R) {
5176 SetVector<StoreInst *> Heads;
5177 SmallDenseSet<StoreInst *> Tails;
5178 SmallDenseMap<StoreInst *, StoreInst *> ConsecutiveChain;
5179
5180 // We may run into multiple chains that merge into a single chain. We mark the
5181 // stores that we vectorized so that we don't visit the same store twice.
5182 BoUpSLP::ValueSet VectorizedStores;
5183 bool Changed = false;
5184
5185 auto &&FindConsecutiveAccess =
5186 [this, &Stores, &Heads, &Tails, &ConsecutiveChain] (int K, int Idx) {
5187 if (!isConsecutiveAccess(Stores[K], Stores[Idx], *DL, *SE))
5188 return false;
5189
5190 Tails.insert(Stores[Idx]);
5191 Heads.insert(Stores[K]);
5192 ConsecutiveChain[Stores[K]] = Stores[Idx];
5193 return true;
5194 };
5195
5196 // Do a quadratic search on all of the given stores in reverse order and find
5197 // all of the pairs of stores that follow each other.
5198 int E = Stores.size();
5199 for (int Idx = E - 1; Idx >= 0; --Idx) {
5200 // If a store has multiple consecutive store candidates, search according
5201 // to the sequence: Idx-1, Idx+1, Idx-2, Idx+2, ...
5202 // This is because usually pairing with immediate succeeding or preceding
5203 // candidate create the best chance to find slp vectorization opportunity.
5204 for (int Offset = 1, F = std::max(E - Idx, Idx + 1); Offset < F; ++Offset)
5205 if ((Idx >= Offset && FindConsecutiveAccess(Idx - Offset, Idx)) ||
5206 (Idx + Offset < E && FindConsecutiveAccess(Idx + Offset, Idx)))
5207 break;
5208 }
5209
5210 // For stores that start but don't end a link in the chain:
5211 for (auto *SI : llvm::reverse(Heads)) {
5212 if (Tails.count(SI))
5213 continue;
5214
5215 // We found a store instr that starts a chain. Now follow the chain and try
5216 // to vectorize it.
5217 BoUpSLP::ValueList Operands;
5218 StoreInst *I = SI;
5219 // Collect the chain into a list.
5220 while ((Tails.count(I) || Heads.count(I)) && !VectorizedStores.count(I)) {
5221 Operands.push_back(I);
5222 // Move to the next value in the chain.
5223 I = ConsecutiveChain[I];
5224 }
5225
5226 // FIXME: Is division-by-2 the correct step? Should we assert that the
5227 // register size is a power-of-2?
5228 for (unsigned Size = R.getMaxVecRegSize(); Size >= R.getMinVecRegSize();
5229 Size /= 2) {
5230 if (vectorizeStoreChain(Operands, R, Size)) {
5231 // Mark the vectorized stores so that we don't vectorize them again.
5232 VectorizedStores.insert(Operands.begin(), Operands.end());
5233 Changed = true;
5234 break;
5235 }
5236 }
5237 }
5238
5239 return Changed;
5240}
5241
5242void SLPVectorizerPass::collectSeedInstructions(BasicBlock *BB) {
5243 // Initialize the collections. We will make a single pass over the block.
5244 Stores.clear();
5245 GEPs.clear();
5246
5247 // Visit the store and getelementptr instructions in BB and organize them in
5248 // Stores and GEPs according to the underlying objects of their pointer
5249 // operands.
5250 for (Instruction &I : *BB) {
5251 // Ignore store instructions that are volatile or have a pointer operand
5252 // that doesn't point to a scalar type.
5253 if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I)) {
5254 if (!SI->isSimple())
5255 continue;
5256 if (!isValidElementType(SI->getValueOperand()->getType()))
5257 continue;
5258 Stores[GetUnderlyingObject(SI->getPointerOperand(), *DL)].push_back(SI);
5259 }
5260
5261 // Ignore getelementptr instructions that have more than one index, a
5262 // constant index, or a pointer operand that doesn't point to a scalar
5263 // type.
5264 else if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(&I)) {
5265 auto Idx = GEP->idx_begin()->get();
5266 if (GEP->getNumIndices() > 1 || isa<Constant>(Idx))
5267 continue;
5268 if (!isValidElementType(Idx->getType()))
5269 continue;
5270 if (GEP->getType()->isVectorTy())
5271 continue;
5272 GEPs[GEP->getPointerOperand()].push_back(GEP);
5273 }
5274 }
5275}
5276
5277bool SLPVectorizerPass::tryToVectorizePair(Value *A, Value *B, BoUpSLP &R) {
5278 if (!A || !B)
5279 return false;
5280 Value *VL[] = { A, B };
5281 return tryToVectorizeList(VL, R, /*UserCost=*/0, true);
5282}
5283
5284bool SLPVectorizerPass::tryToVectorizeList(ArrayRef<Value *> VL, BoUpSLP &R,
5285 int UserCost, bool AllowReorder) {
5286 if (VL.size() < 2)
5287 return false;
5288
5289 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Trying to vectorize a list of length = "
5290 << VL.size() << ".\n");
5291
5292 // Check that all of the parts are scalar instructions of the same type,
5293 // we permit an alternate opcode via InstructionsState.
5294 InstructionsState S = getSameOpcode(VL);
5295 if (!S.getOpcode())
5296 return false;
5297
5298 Instruction *I0 = cast<Instruction>(S.OpValue);
5299 unsigned Sz = R.getVectorElementSize(I0);
5300 unsigned MinVF = std::max(2U, R.getMinVecRegSize() / Sz);
5301 unsigned MaxVF = std::max<unsigned>(PowerOf2Floor(VL.size()), MinVF);
5302 if (MaxVF < 2) {
5303 R.getORE()->emit([&]() {
5304 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(SV_NAME, "SmallVF", I0)
5305 << "Cannot SLP vectorize list: vectorization factor "
5306 << "less than 2 is not supported";
5307 });
5308 return false;
5309 }
5310
5311 for (Value *V : VL) {
5312 Type *Ty = V->getType();
5313 if (!isValidElementType(Ty)) {
5314 // NOTE: the following will give user internal llvm type name, which may
5315 // not be useful.
5316 R.getORE()->emit([&]() {
5317 std::string type_str;
5318 llvm::raw_string_ostream rso(type_str);
5319 Ty->print(rso);
5320 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(SV_NAME, "UnsupportedType", I0)
5321 << "Cannot SLP vectorize list: type "
5322 << rso.str() + " is unsupported by vectorizer";
5323 });
5324 return false;
5325 }
5326 }
5327
5328 bool Changed = false;
5329 bool CandidateFound = false;
5330 int MinCost = SLPCostThreshold;
5331
5332 // Keep track of values that were deleted by vectorizing in the loop below.
5333 SmallVector<WeakTrackingVH, 8> TrackValues(VL.begin(), VL.end());
5334
5335 unsigned NextInst = 0, MaxInst = VL.size();
5336 for (unsigned VF = MaxVF; NextInst + 1 < MaxInst && VF >= MinVF;
5337 VF /= 2) {
5338 // No actual vectorization should happen, if number of parts is the same as
5339 // provided vectorization factor (i.e. the scalar type is used for vector
5340 // code during codegen).
5341 auto *VecTy = VectorType::get(VL[0]->getType(), VF);
5342 if (TTI->getNumberOfParts(VecTy) == VF)
5343 continue;
5344 for (unsigned I = NextInst; I < MaxInst; ++I) {
5345 unsigned OpsWidth = 0;
5346
5347 if (I + VF > MaxInst)
5348 OpsWidth = MaxInst - I;
5349 else
5350 OpsWidth = VF;
5351
5352 if (!isPowerOf2_32(OpsWidth) || OpsWidth < 2)
5353 break;
5354
5355 // Check that a previous iteration of this loop did not delete the Value.
5356 if (hasValueBeenRAUWed(VL, TrackValues, I, OpsWidth))
5357 continue;
5358
5359 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Analyzing " << OpsWidth << " operations "
5360 << "\n");
5361 ArrayRef<Value *> Ops = VL.slice(I, OpsWidth);
5362
5363 R.buildTree(Ops);
5364 Optional<ArrayRef<unsigned>> Order = R.bestOrder();
5365 // TODO: check if we can allow reordering for more cases.
5366 if (AllowReorder && Order) {
5367 // TODO: reorder tree nodes without tree rebuilding.
5368 // Conceptually, there is nothing actually preventing us from trying to
5369 // reorder a larger list. In fact, we do exactly this when vectorizing
5370 // reductions. However, at this point, we only expect to get here when
5371 // there are exactly two operations.
5372 assert(Ops.size() == 2);
5373 Value *ReorderedOps[] = {Ops[1], Ops[0]};
5374 R.buildTree(ReorderedOps, None);
5375 }
5376 if (R.isTreeTinyAndNotFullyVectorizable())
5377 continue;
5378
5379 R.computeMinimumValueSizes();
5380 int Cost = R.getTreeCost() - UserCost;
5381 CandidateFound = true;
5382 MinCost = std::min(MinCost, Cost);
5383
5384 if (Cost < -SLPCostThreshold) {
5385 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Vectorizing list at cost:" << Cost << ".\n");
5386 R.getORE()->emit(OptimizationRemark(SV_NAME, "VectorizedList",
5387 cast<Instruction>(Ops[0]))
5388 << "SLP vectorized with cost " << ore::NV("Cost", Cost)
5389 << " and with tree size "
5390 << ore::NV("TreeSize", R.getTreeSize()));
5391
5392 R.vectorizeTree();
5393 // Move to the next bundle.
5394 I += VF - 1;
5395 NextInst = I + 1;
5396 Changed = true;
5397 }
5398 }
5399 }
5400
5401 if (!Changed && CandidateFound) {
5402 R.getORE()->emit([&]() {
5403 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(SV_NAME, "NotBeneficial", I0)
5404 << "List vectorization was possible but not beneficial with cost "
5405 << ore::NV("Cost", MinCost) << " >= "
5406 << ore::NV("Treshold", -SLPCostThreshold);
5407 });
5408 } else if (!Changed) {
5409 R.getORE()->emit([&]() {
5410 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(SV_NAME, "NotPossible", I0)
5411 << "Cannot SLP vectorize list: vectorization was impossible"
5412 << " with available vectorization factors";
5413 });
5414 }
5415 return Changed;
5416}
5417
5418bool SLPVectorizerPass::tryToVectorize(Instruction *I, BoUpSLP &R) {
5419 if (!I)
5420 return false;
5421
5422 if (!isa<BinaryOperator>(I) && !isa<CmpInst>(I))
5423 return false;
5424
5425 Value *P = I->getParent();
5426
5427 // Vectorize in current basic block only.
5428 auto *Op0 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(I->getOperand(0));
5429 auto *Op1 = dyn_cast<Instruction>(I->getOperand(1));
5430 if (!Op0 || !Op1 || Op0->getParent() != P || Op1->getParent() != P)
5431 return false;
5432
5433 // Try to vectorize V.
5434 if (tryToVectorizePair(Op0, Op1, R))
5435 return true;
5436
5437 auto *A = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Op0);
5438 auto *B = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Op1);
5439 // Try to skip B.
5440 if (B && B->hasOneUse()) {
5441 auto *B0 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(B->getOperand(0));
5442 auto *B1 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(B->getOperand(1));
5443 if (B0 && B0->getParent() == P && tryToVectorizePair(A, B0, R))
5444 return true;
5445 if (B1 && B1->getParent() == P && tryToVectorizePair(A, B1, R))
5446 return true;
5447 }
5448
5449 // Try to skip A.
5450 if (A && A->hasOneUse()) {
5451 auto *A0 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(A->getOperand(0));
5452 auto *A1 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(A->getOperand(1));
5453 if (A0 && A0->getParent() == P && tryToVectorizePair(A0, B, R))
5454 return true;
5455 if (A1 && A1->getParent() == P && tryToVectorizePair(A1, B, R))
5456 return true;
5457 }
5458 return false;
5459}
5460
5461/// Generate a shuffle mask to be used in a reduction tree.
5462///
5463/// \param VecLen The length of the vector to be reduced.
5464/// \param NumEltsToRdx The number of elements that should be reduced in the
5465/// vector.
5466/// \param IsPairwise Whether the reduction is a pairwise or splitting
5467/// reduction. A pairwise reduction will generate a mask of
5468/// <0,2,...> or <1,3,..> while a splitting reduction will generate
5469/// <2,3, undef,undef> for a vector of 4 and NumElts = 2.
5470/// \param IsLeft True will generate a mask of even elements, odd otherwise.
5471static Value *createRdxShuffleMask(unsigned VecLen, unsigned NumEltsToRdx,
5472 bool IsPairwise, bool IsLeft,
5473 IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
5474 assert((IsPairwise || !IsLeft) && "Don't support a <0,1,undef,...> mask");
5475
5476 SmallVector<Constant *, 32> ShuffleMask(
5477 VecLen, UndefValue::get(Builder.getInt32Ty()));
5478
5479 if (IsPairwise)
5480 // Build a mask of 0, 2, ... (left) or 1, 3, ... (right).
5481 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumEltsToRdx; ++i)
5482 ShuffleMask[i] = Builder.getInt32(2 * i + !IsLeft);
5483 else
5484 // Move the upper half of the vector to the lower half.
5485 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumEltsToRdx; ++i)
5486 ShuffleMask[i] = Builder.getInt32(NumEltsToRdx + i);
5487
5488 return ConstantVector::get(ShuffleMask);
5489}
5490
5491namespace {
5492
5493/// Model horizontal reductions.
5494///
5495/// A horizontal reduction is a tree of reduction operations (currently add and
5496/// fadd) that has operations that can be put into a vector as its leaf.
5497/// For example, this tree:
5498///
5499/// mul mul mul mul
5500/// \ / \ /
5501/// + +
5502/// \ /
5503/// +
5504/// This tree has "mul" as its reduced values and "+" as its reduction
5505/// operations. A reduction might be feeding into a store or a binary operation
5506/// feeding a phi.
5507/// ...
5508/// \ /
5509/// +
5510/// |
5511/// phi +=
5512///
5513/// Or:
5514/// ...
5515/// \ /
5516/// +
5517/// |
5518/// *p =
5519///
5520class HorizontalReduction {
5521 using ReductionOpsType = SmallVector<Value *, 16>;
5522 using ReductionOpsListType = SmallVector<ReductionOpsType, 2>;
5523 ReductionOpsListType ReductionOps;
5524 SmallVector<Value *, 32> ReducedVals;
5525 // Use map vector to make stable output.
5526 MapVector<Instruction *, Value *> ExtraArgs;
5527
5528 /// Kind of the reduction data.
5529 enum ReductionKind {
5530 RK_None, /// Not a reduction.
5531 RK_Arithmetic, /// Binary reduction data.
5532 RK_Min, /// Minimum reduction data.
5533 RK_UMin, /// Unsigned minimum reduction data.
5534 RK_Max, /// Maximum reduction data.
5535 RK_UMax, /// Unsigned maximum reduction data.
5536 };
5537
5538 /// Contains info about operation, like its opcode, left and right operands.
5539 class OperationData {
5540 /// Opcode of the instruction.
5541 unsigned Opcode = 0;
5542
5543 /// Left operand of the reduction operation.
5544 Value *LHS = nullptr;
5545
5546 /// Right operand of the reduction operation.
5547 Value *RHS = nullptr;
5548
5549 /// Kind of the reduction operation.
5550 ReductionKind Kind = RK_None;
5551
5552 /// True if float point min/max reduction has no NaNs.
5553 bool NoNaN = false;
5554
5555 /// Checks if the reduction operation can be vectorized.
5556 bool isVectorizable() const {
5557 return LHS && RHS &&
5558 // We currently only support add/mul/logical && min/max reductions.
5559 ((Kind == RK_Arithmetic &&
5560 (Opcode == Instruction::Add || Opcode == Instruction::FAdd ||
5561 Opcode == Instruction::Mul || Opcode == Instruction::FMul ||
5562 Opcode == Instruction::And || Opcode == Instruction::Or ||
5563 Opcode == Instruction::Xor)) ||
5564 ((Opcode == Instruction::ICmp || Opcode == Instruction::FCmp) &&
5565 (Kind == RK_Min || Kind == RK_Max)) ||
5566 (Opcode == Instruction::ICmp &&
5567 (Kind == RK_UMin || Kind == RK_UMax)));
5568 }
5569
5570 /// Creates reduction operation with the current opcode.
5571 Value *createOp(IRBuilder<> &Builder, const Twine &Name) const {
5572 assert(isVectorizable() &&
5573 "Expected add|fadd or min/max reduction operation.");
5574 Value *Cmp;
5575 switch (Kind) {
5576 case RK_Arithmetic:
5577 return Builder.CreateBinOp((Instruction::BinaryOps)Opcode, LHS, RHS,
5578 Name);
5579 case RK_Min:
5580 Cmp = Opcode == Instruction::ICmp ? Builder.CreateICmpSLT(LHS, RHS)
5581 : Builder.CreateFCmpOLT(LHS, RHS);
5582 break;
5583 case RK_Max:
5584 Cmp = Opcode == Instruction::ICmp ? Builder.CreateICmpSGT(LHS, RHS)
5585 : Builder.CreateFCmpOGT(LHS, RHS);
5586 break;
5587 case RK_UMin:
5588 assert(Opcode == Instruction::ICmp && "Expected integer types.");
5589 Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpULT(LHS, RHS);
5590 break;
5591 case RK_UMax:
5592 assert(Opcode == Instruction::ICmp && "Expected integer types.");
5593 Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpUGT(LHS, RHS);
5594 break;
5595 case RK_None:
5596 llvm_unreachable("Unknown reduction operation.");
5597 }
5598 return Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, LHS, RHS, Name);
5599 }
5600
5601 public:
5602 explicit OperationData() = default;
5603
5604 /// Construction for reduced values. They are identified by opcode only and
5605 /// don't have associated LHS/RHS values.
5606 explicit OperationData(Value *V) {
5607 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V))
5608 Opcode = I->getOpcode();
5609 }
5610
5611 /// Constructor for reduction operations with opcode and its left and
5612 /// right operands.
5613 OperationData(unsigned Opcode, Value *LHS, Value *RHS, ReductionKind Kind,
5614 bool NoNaN = false)
5615 : Opcode(Opcode), LHS(LHS), RHS(RHS), Kind(Kind), NoNaN(NoNaN) {
5616 assert(Kind != RK_None && "One of the reduction operations is expected.");
5617 }
5618
5619 explicit operator bool() const { return Opcode; }
5620
5621 /// Get the index of the first operand.
5622 unsigned getFirstOperandIndex() const {
5623 assert(!!*this && "The opcode is not set.");
5624 switch (Kind) {
5625 case RK_Min:
5626 case RK_UMin:
5627 case RK_Max:
5628 case RK_UMax:
5629 return 1;
5630 case RK_Arithmetic:
5631 case RK_None:
5632 break;
5633 }
5634 return 0;
5635 }
5636
5637 /// Total number of operands in the reduction operation.
5638 unsigned getNumberOfOperands() const {
5639 assert(Kind != RK_None && !!*this && LHS && RHS &&
5640 "Expected reduction operation.");
5641 switch (Kind) {
5642 case RK_Arithmetic:
5643 return 2;
5644 case RK_Min:
5645 case RK_UMin:
5646 case RK_Max:
5647 case RK_UMax:
5648 return 3;
5649 case RK_None:
5650 break;
5651 }
5652 llvm_unreachable("Reduction kind is not set");
5653 }
5654
5655 /// Checks if the operation has the same parent as \p P.
5656 bool hasSameParent(Instruction *I, Value *P, bool IsRedOp) const {
5657 assert(Kind != RK_None && !!*this && LHS && RHS &&
5658 "Expected reduction operation.");
5659 if (!IsRedOp)
5660 return I->getParent() == P;
5661 switch (Kind) {
5662 case RK_Arithmetic:
5663 // Arithmetic reduction operation must be used once only.
5664 return I->getParent() == P;
5665 case RK_Min:
5666 case RK_UMin:
5667 case RK_Max:
5668 case RK_UMax: {
5669 // SelectInst must be used twice while the condition op must have single
5670 // use only.
5671 auto *Cmp = cast<Instruction>(cast<SelectInst>(I)->getCondition());
5672 return I->getParent() == P && Cmp && Cmp->getParent() == P;
5673 }
5674 case RK_None:
5675 break;
5676 }
5677 llvm_unreachable("Reduction kind is not set");
5678 }
5679 /// Expected number of uses for reduction operations/reduced values.
5680 bool hasRequiredNumberOfUses(Instruction *I, bool IsReductionOp) const {
5681 assert(Kind != RK_None && !!*this && LHS && RHS &&
5682 "Expected reduction operation.");
5683 switch (Kind) {
5684 case RK_Arithmetic:
5685 return I->hasOneUse();
5686 case RK_Min:
5687 case RK_UMin:
5688 case RK_Max:
5689 case RK_UMax:
5690 return I->hasNUses(2) &&
5691 (!IsReductionOp ||
5692 cast<SelectInst>(I)->getCondition()->hasOneUse());
5693 case RK_None:
5694 break;
5695 }
5696 llvm_unreachable("Reduction kind is not set");
5697 }
5698
5699 /// Initializes the list of reduction operations.
5700 void initReductionOps(ReductionOpsListType &ReductionOps) {
5701 assert(Kind != RK_None && !!*this && LHS && RHS &&
5702 "Expected reduction operation.");
5703 switch (Kind) {
5704 case RK_Arithmetic:
5705 ReductionOps.assign(1, ReductionOpsType());
5706 break;
5707 case RK_Min:
5708 case RK_UMin:
5709 case RK_Max:
5710 case RK_UMax:
5711 ReductionOps.assign(2, ReductionOpsType());
5712 break;
5713 case RK_None:
5714 llvm_unreachable("Reduction kind is not set");
5715 }
5716 }
5717 /// Add all reduction operations for the reduction instruction \p I.
5718 void addReductionOps(Instruction *I, ReductionOpsListType &ReductionOps) {
5719 assert(Kind != RK_None && !!*this && LHS && RHS &&
5720 "Expected reduction operation.");
5721 switch (Kind) {
5722 case RK_Arithmetic:
5723 ReductionOps[0].emplace_back(I);
5724 break;
5725 case RK_Min:
5726 case RK_UMin:
5727 case RK_Max:
5728 case RK_UMax:
5729 ReductionOps[0].emplace_back(cast<SelectInst>(I)->getCondition());
5730 ReductionOps[1].emplace_back(I);
5731 break;
5732 case RK_None:
5733 llvm_unreachable("Reduction kind is not set");
5734 }
5735 }
5736
5737 /// Checks if instruction is associative and can be vectorized.
5738 bool isAssociative(Instruction *I) const {
5739 assert(Kind != RK_None && *this && LHS && RHS &&
5740 "Expected reduction operation.");
5741 switch (Kind) {
5742 case RK_Arithmetic:
5743 return I->isAssociative();
5744 case RK_Min:
5745 case RK_Max:
5746 return Opcode == Instruction::ICmp ||
5747 cast<Instruction>(I->getOperand(0))->isFast();
5748 case RK_UMin:
5749 case RK_UMax:
5750 assert(Opcode == Instruction::ICmp &&
5751 "Only integer compare operation is expected.");
5752 return true;
5753 case RK_None:
5754 break;
5755 }
5756 llvm_unreachable("Reduction kind is not set");
5757 }
5758
5759 /// Checks if the reduction operation can be vectorized.
5760 bool isVectorizable(Instruction *I) const {
5761 return isVectorizable() && isAssociative(I);
5762 }
5763
5764 /// Checks if two operation data are both a reduction op or both a reduced
5765 /// value.
5766 bool operator==(const OperationData &OD) {
5767 assert(((Kind != OD.Kind) || ((!LHS == !OD.LHS) && (!RHS == !OD.RHS))) &&
5768 "One of the comparing operations is incorrect.");
5769 return this == &OD || (Kind == OD.Kind && Opcode == OD.Opcode);
5770 }
5771 bool operator!=(const OperationData &OD) { return !(*this == OD); }
5772 void clear() {
5773 Opcode = 0;
5774 LHS = nullptr;
5775 RHS = nullptr;
5776 Kind = RK_None;
5777 NoNaN = false;
5778 }
5779
5780 /// Get the opcode of the reduction operation.
5781 unsigned getOpcode() const {
5782 assert(isVectorizable() && "Expected vectorizable operation.");
5783 return Opcode;
5784 }
5785
5786 /// Get kind of reduction data.
5787 ReductionKind getKind() const { return Kind; }
5788 Value *getLHS() const { return LHS; }
5789 Value *getRHS() const { return RHS; }
5790 Type *getConditionType() const {
5791 switch (Kind) {
5792 case RK_Arithmetic:
5793 return nullptr;
5794 case RK_Min:
5795 case RK_Max:
5796 case RK_UMin:
5797 case RK_UMax:
5798 return CmpInst::makeCmpResultType(LHS->getType());
5799 case RK_None:
5800 break;
5801 }
5802 llvm_unreachable("Reduction kind is not set");
5803 }
5804
5805 /// Creates reduction operation with the current opcode with the IR flags
5806 /// from \p ReductionOps.
5807 Value *createOp(IRBuilder<> &Builder, const Twine &Name,
5808 const ReductionOpsListType &ReductionOps) const {
5809 assert(isVectorizable() &&
5810 "Expected add|fadd or min/max reduction operation.");
5811 auto *Op = createOp(Builder, Name);
5812 switch (Kind) {
5813 case RK_Arithmetic:
5814 propagateIRFlags(Op, ReductionOps[0]);
5815 return Op;
5816 case RK_Min:
5817 case RK_Max:
5818 case RK_UMin:
5819 case RK_UMax:
5820 if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(Op))
5821 propagateIRFlags(SI->getCondition(), ReductionOps[0]);
5822 propagateIRFlags(Op, ReductionOps[1]);
5823 return Op;
5824 case RK_None:
5825 break;
5826 }
5827 llvm_unreachable("Unknown reduction operation.");
5828 }
5829 /// Creates reduction operation with the current opcode with the IR flags
5830 /// from \p I.
5831 Value *createOp(IRBuilder<> &Builder, const Twine &Name,
5832 Instruction *I) const {
5833 assert(isVectorizable() &&
5834 "Expected add|fadd or min/max reduction operation.");
5835 auto *Op = createOp(Builder, Name);
5836 switch (Kind) {
5837 case RK_Arithmetic:
5838 propagateIRFlags(Op, I);
5839 return Op;
5840 case RK_Min:
5841 case RK_Max:
5842 case RK_UMin:
5843 case RK_UMax:
5844 if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(Op)) {
5845 propagateIRFlags(SI->getCondition(),
5846 cast<SelectInst>(I)->getCondition());
5847 }
5848 propagateIRFlags(Op, I);
5849 return Op;
5850 case RK_None:
5851 break;
5852 }
5853 llvm_unreachable("Unknown reduction operation.");
5854 }
5855
5856 TargetTransformInfo::ReductionFlags getFlags() const {
5857 TargetTransformInfo::ReductionFlags Flags;
5858 Flags.NoNaN = NoNaN;
5859 switch (Kind) {
5860 case RK_Arithmetic:
5861 break;
5862 case RK_Min:
5863 Flags.IsSigned = Opcode == Instruction::ICmp;
5864 Flags.IsMaxOp = false;
5865 break;
5866 case RK_Max:
5867 Flags.IsSigned = Opcode == Instruction::ICmp;
5868 Flags.IsMaxOp = true;
5869 break;
5870 case RK_UMin:
5871 Flags.IsSigned = false;
5872 Flags.IsMaxOp = false;
5873 break;
5874 case RK_UMax:
5875 Flags.IsSigned = false;
5876 Flags.IsMaxOp = true;
5877 break;
5878 case RK_None:
5879 llvm_unreachable("Reduction kind is not set");
5880 }
5881 return Flags;
5882 }
5883 };
5884
5885 WeakTrackingVH ReductionRoot;
5886
5887 /// The operation data of the reduction operation.
5888 OperationData ReductionData;
5889
5890 /// The operation data of the values we perform a reduction on.
5891 OperationData ReducedValueData;
5892
5893 /// Should we model this reduction as a pairwise reduction tree or a tree that
5894 /// splits the vector in halves and adds those halves.
5895 bool IsPairwiseReduction = false;
5896
5897 /// Checks if the ParentStackElem.first should be marked as a reduction
5898 /// operation with an extra argument or as extra argument itself.
5899 void markExtraArg(std::pair<Instruction *, unsigned> &ParentStackElem,
5900 Value *ExtraArg) {
5901 if (ExtraArgs.count(ParentStackElem.first)) {
5902 ExtraArgs[ParentStackElem.first] = nullptr;
5903 // We ran into something like:
5904 // ParentStackElem.first = ExtraArgs[ParentStackElem.first] + ExtraArg.
5905 // The whole ParentStackElem.first should be considered as an extra value
5906 // in this case.
5907 // Do not perform analysis of remaining operands of ParentStackElem.first
5908 // instruction, this whole instruction is an extra argument.
5909 ParentStackElem.second = ParentStackElem.first->getNumOperands();
5910 } else {
5911 // We ran into something like:
5912 // ParentStackElem.first += ... + ExtraArg + ...
5913 ExtraArgs[ParentStackElem.first] = ExtraArg;
5914 }
5915 }
5916
5917 static OperationData getOperationData(Value *V) {
5918 if (!V)
5919 return OperationData();
5920
5921 Value *LHS;
5922 Value *RHS;
5923 if (m_BinOp(m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS)).match(V)) {
5924 return OperationData(cast<BinaryOperator>(V)->getOpcode(), LHS, RHS,
5925 RK_Arithmetic);
5926 }
5927 if (auto *Select = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(V)) {
5928 // Look for a min/max pattern.
5929 if (m_UMin(m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS)).match(Select)) {
5930 return OperationData(Instruction::ICmp, LHS, RHS, RK_UMin);
5931 } else if (m_SMin(m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS)).match(Select)) {
5932 return OperationData(Instruction::ICmp, LHS, RHS, RK_Min);
5933 } else if (m_OrdFMin(m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS)).match(Select) ||
5934 m_UnordFMin(m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS)).match(Select)) {
5935 return OperationData(
5936 Instruction::FCmp, LHS, RHS, RK_Min,
5937 cast<Instruction>(Select->getCondition())->hasNoNaNs());
5938 } else if (m_UMax(m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS)).match(Select)) {
5939 return OperationData(Instruction::ICmp, LHS, RHS, RK_UMax);
5940 } else if (m_SMax(m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS)).match(Select)) {
5941 return OperationData(Instruction::ICmp, LHS, RHS, RK_Max);
5942 } else if (m_OrdFMax(m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS)).match(Select) ||
5943 m_UnordFMax(m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS)).match(Select)) {
5944 return OperationData(
5945 Instruction::FCmp, LHS, RHS, RK_Max,
5946 cast<Instruction>(Select->getCondition())->hasNoNaNs());
5947 } else {
5948 // Try harder: look for min/max pattern based on instructions producing
5949 // same values such as: select ((cmp Inst1, Inst2), Inst1, Inst2).
5950 // During the intermediate stages of SLP, it's very common to have
5951 // pattern like this (since optimizeGatherSequence is run only once
5952 // at the end):
5953 // %1 = extractelement <2 x i32> %a, i32 0
5954 // %2 = extractelement <2 x i32> %a, i32 1
5955 // %cond = icmp sgt i32 %1, %2
5956 // %3 = extractelement <2 x i32> %a, i32 0
5957 // %4 = extractelement <2 x i32> %a, i32 1
5958 // %select = select i1 %cond, i32 %3, i32 %4
5959 CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
5960 Instruction *L1;
5961 Instruction *L2;
5962
5963 LHS = Select->getTrueValue();
5964 RHS = Select->getFalseValue();
5965 Value *Cond = Select->getCondition();
5966
5967 // TODO: Support inverse predicates.
5968 if (match(Cond, m_Cmp(Pred, m_Specific(LHS), m_Instruction(L2)))) {
5969 if (!isa<ExtractElementInst>(RHS) ||
5970 !L2->isIdenticalTo(cast<Instruction>(RHS)))
5971 return OperationData(V);
5972 } else if (match(Cond, m_Cmp(Pred, m_Instruction(L1), m_Specific(RHS)))) {
5973 if (!isa<ExtractElementInst>(LHS) ||
5974 !L1->isIdenticalTo(cast<Instruction>(LHS)))
5975 return OperationData(V);
5976 } else {
5977 if (!isa<ExtractElementInst>(LHS) || !isa<ExtractElementInst>(RHS))
5978 return OperationData(V);
5979 if (!match(Cond, m_Cmp(Pred, m_Instruction(L1), m_Instruction(L2))) ||
5980 !L1->isIdenticalTo(cast<Instruction>(LHS)) ||
5981 !L2->isIdenticalTo(cast<Instruction>(RHS)))
5982 return OperationData(V);
5983 }
5984 switch (Pred) {
5985 default:
5986 return OperationData(V);
5987
5988 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
5989 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
5990 return OperationData(Instruction::ICmp, LHS, RHS, RK_UMin);
5991
5992 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
5993 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
5994 return OperationData(Instruction::ICmp, LHS, RHS, RK_Min);
5995
5996 case CmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
5997 case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
5998 case CmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
5999 case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
6000 return OperationData(Instruction::FCmp, LHS, RHS, RK_Min,
6001 cast<Instruction>(Cond)->hasNoNaNs());
6002
6003 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
6004 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
6005 return OperationData(Instruction::ICmp, LHS, RHS, RK_UMax);
6006
6007 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
6008 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
6009 return OperationData(Instruction::ICmp, LHS, RHS, RK_Max);
6010
6011 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
6012 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE:
6013 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
6014 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
6015 return OperationData(Instruction::FCmp, LHS, RHS, RK_Max,
6016 cast<Instruction>(Cond)->hasNoNaNs());
6017 }
6018 }
6019 }
6020 return OperationData(V);
6021 }
6022
6023public:
6024 HorizontalReduction() = default;
6025
6026 /// Try to find a reduction tree.
6027 bool matchAssociativeReduction(PHINode *Phi, Instruction *B) {
6028 assert((!Phi || is_contained(Phi->operands(), B)) &&
6029 "Thi phi needs to use the binary operator");
6030
6031 ReductionData = getOperationData(B);
6032
6033 // We could have a initial reductions that is not an add.
6034 // r *= v1 + v2 + v3 + v4
6035 // In such a case start looking for a tree rooted in the first '+'.
6036 if (Phi) {
6037 if (ReductionData.getLHS() == Phi) {
6038 Phi = nullptr;
6039 B = dyn_cast<Instruction>(ReductionData.getRHS());
6040 ReductionData = getOperationData(B);
6041 } else if (ReductionData.getRHS() == Phi) {
6042 Phi = nullptr;
6043 B = dyn_cast<Instruction>(ReductionData.getLHS());
6044 ReductionData = getOperationData(B);
6045 }
6046 }
6047
6048 if (!ReductionData.isVectorizable(B))
6049 return false;
6050
6051 Type *Ty = B->getType();
6052 if (!isValidElementType(Ty))
6053 return false;
6054 if (!Ty->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && !Ty->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
6055 return false;
6056
6057 ReducedValueData.clear();
6058 ReductionRoot = B;
6059
6060 // Post order traverse the reduction tree starting at B. We only handle true
6061 // trees containing only binary operators.
6062 SmallVector<std::pair<Instruction *, unsigned>, 32> Stack;
6063 Stack.push_back(std::make_pair(B, ReductionData.getFirstOperandIndex()));
6064 ReductionData.initReductionOps(ReductionOps);
6065 while (!Stack.empty()) {
6066 Instruction *TreeN = Stack.back().first;
6067 unsigned EdgeToVist = Stack.back().second++;
6068 OperationData OpData = getOperationData(TreeN);
6069 bool IsReducedValue = OpData != ReductionData;
6070
6071 // Postorder vist.
6072 if (IsReducedValue || EdgeToVist == OpData.getNumberOfOperands()) {
6073 if (IsReducedValue)
6074 ReducedVals.push_back(TreeN);
6075 else {
6076 auto I = ExtraArgs.find(TreeN);
6077 if (I != ExtraArgs.end() && !I->second) {
6078 // Check if TreeN is an extra argument of its parent operation.
6079 if (Stack.size() <= 1) {
6080 // TreeN can't be an extra argument as it is a root reduction
6081 // operation.
6082 return false;
6083 }
6084 // Yes, TreeN is an extra argument, do not add it to a list of
6085 // reduction operations.
6086 // Stack[Stack.size() - 2] always points to the parent operation.
6087 markExtraArg(Stack[Stack.size() - 2], TreeN);
6088 ExtraArgs.erase(TreeN);
6089 } else
6090 ReductionData.addReductionOps(TreeN, ReductionOps);
6091 }
6092 // Retract.
6093 Stack.pop_back();
6094 continue;
6095 }
6096
6097 // Visit left or right.
6098 Value *NextV = TreeN->getOperand(EdgeToVist);
6099 if (NextV != Phi) {
6100 auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(NextV);
6101 OpData = getOperationData(I);
6102 // Continue analysis if the next operand is a reduction operation or
6103 // (possibly) a reduced value. If the reduced value opcode is not set,
6104 // the first met operation != reduction operation is considered as the
6105 // reduced value class.
6106 if (I && (!ReducedValueData || OpData == ReducedValueData ||
6107 OpData == ReductionData)) {
6108 const bool IsReductionOperation = OpData == ReductionData;
6109 // Only handle trees in the current basic block.
6110 if (!ReductionData.hasSameParent(I, B->getParent(),
6111 IsReductionOperation)) {
6112 // I is an extra argument for TreeN (its parent operation).
6113 markExtraArg(Stack.back(), I);
6114 continue;
6115 }
6116
6117 // Each tree node needs to have minimal number of users except for the
6118 // ultimate reduction.
6119 if (!ReductionData.hasRequiredNumberOfUses(I,
6120 OpData == ReductionData) &&
6121 I != B) {
6122 // I is an extra argument for TreeN (its parent operation).
6123 markExtraArg(Stack.back(), I);
6124 continue;
6125 }
6126
6127 if (IsReductionOperation) {
6128 // We need to be able to reassociate the reduction operations.
6129 if (!OpData.isAssociative(I)) {
6130 // I is an extra argument for TreeN (its parent operation).
6131 markExtraArg(Stack.back(), I);
6132 continue;
6133 }
6134 } else if (ReducedValueData &&
6135 ReducedValueData != OpData) {
6136 // Make sure that the opcodes of the operations that we are going to
6137 // reduce match.
6138 // I is an extra argument for TreeN (its parent operation).
6139 markExtraArg(Stack.back(), I);
6140 continue;
6141 } else if (!ReducedValueData)
6142 ReducedValueData = OpData;
6143
6144 Stack.push_back(std::make_pair(I, OpData.getFirstOperandIndex()));
6145 continue;
6146 }
6147 }
6148 // NextV is an extra argument for TreeN (its parent operation).
6149 markExtraArg(Stack.back(), NextV);
6150 }
6151 return true;
6152 }
6153
6154 /// Attempt to vectorize the tree found by
6155 /// matchAssociativeReduction.
6156 bool tryToReduce(BoUpSLP &V, TargetTransformInfo *TTI) {
6157 if (ReducedVals.empty())
6158 return false;
6159
6160 // If there is a sufficient number of reduction values, reduce
6161 // to a nearby power-of-2. Can safely generate oversized
6162 // vectors and rely on the backend to split them to legal sizes.
6163 unsigned NumReducedVals = ReducedVals.size();
6164 if (NumReducedVals < 4)
6165 return false;
6166
6167 unsigned ReduxWidth = PowerOf2Floor(NumReducedVals);
6168
6169 Value *VectorizedTree = nullptr;
6170
6171 // FIXME: Fast-math-flags should be set based on the instructions in the
6172 // reduction (not all of 'fast' are required).
6173 IRBuilder<> Builder(cast<Instruction>(ReductionRoot));
6174 FastMathFlags Unsafe;
6175 Unsafe.setFast();
6176 Builder.setFastMathFlags(Unsafe);
6177 unsigned i = 0;
6178
6179 BoUpSLP::ExtraValueToDebugLocsMap ExternallyUsedValues;
6180 // The same extra argument may be used several time, so log each attempt
6181 // to use it.
6182 for (auto &Pair : ExtraArgs) {
6183 assert(Pair.first && "DebugLoc must be set.");
6184 ExternallyUsedValues[Pair.second].push_back(Pair.first);
6185 }
6186 // The reduction root is used as the insertion point for new instructions,
6187 // so set it as externally used to prevent it from being deleted.
6188 ExternallyUsedValues[ReductionRoot];
6189 SmallVector<Value *, 16> IgnoreList;
6190 for (auto &V : ReductionOps)
6191 IgnoreList.append(V.begin(), V.end());
6192 while (i < NumReducedVals - ReduxWidth + 1 && ReduxWidth > 2) {
6193 auto VL = makeArrayRef(&ReducedVals[i], ReduxWidth);
6194 V.buildTree(VL, ExternallyUsedValues, IgnoreList);
6195 Optional<ArrayRef<unsigned>> Order = V.bestOrder();
6196 // TODO: Handle orders of size less than number of elements in the vector.
6197 if (Order && Order->size() == VL.size()) {
6198 // TODO: reorder tree nodes without tree rebuilding.
6199 SmallVector<Value *, 4> ReorderedOps(VL.size());
6200 llvm::transform(*Order, ReorderedOps.begin(),
6201 [VL](const unsigned Idx) { return VL[Idx]; });
6202 V.buildTree(ReorderedOps, ExternallyUsedValues, IgnoreList);
6203 }
6204 if (V.isTreeTinyAndNotFullyVectorizable())
6205 break;
6206
6207 V.computeMinimumValueSizes();
6208
6209 // Estimate cost.
6210 int TreeCost = V.getTreeCost();
6211 int ReductionCost = getReductionCost(TTI, ReducedVals[i], ReduxWidth);
6212 int Cost = TreeCost + ReductionCost;
6213 if (Cost >= -SLPCostThreshold) {
6214 V.getORE()->emit([&]() {
6215 return OptimizationRemarkMissed(
6216 SV_NAME, "HorSLPNotBeneficial", cast<Instruction>(VL[0]))
6217 << "Vectorizing horizontal reduction is possible"
6218 << "but not beneficial with cost "
6219 << ore::NV("Cost", Cost) << " and threshold "
6220 << ore::NV("Threshold", -SLPCostThreshold);
6221 });
6222 break;
6223 }
6224
6225 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Vectorizing horizontal reduction at cost:"
6226 << Cost << ". (HorRdx)\n");
6227 V.getORE()->emit([&]() {
6228 return OptimizationRemark(
6229 SV_NAME, "VectorizedHorizontalReduction", cast<Instruction>(VL[0]))
6230 << "Vectorized horizontal reduction with cost "
6231 << ore::NV("Cost", Cost) << " and with tree size "
6232 << ore::NV("TreeSize", V.getTreeSize());
6233 });
6234
6235 // Vectorize a tree.
6236 DebugLoc Loc = cast<Instruction>(ReducedVals[i])->getDebugLoc();
6237 Value *VectorizedRoot = V.vectorizeTree(ExternallyUsedValues);
6238
6239 // Emit a reduction.
6240 Builder.SetInsertPoint(cast<Instruction>(ReductionRoot));
6241 Value *ReducedSubTree =
6242 emitReduction(VectorizedRoot, Builder, ReduxWidth, TTI);
6243 if (VectorizedTree) {
6244 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(Loc);
6245 OperationData VectReductionData(ReductionData.getOpcode(),
6246 VectorizedTree, ReducedSubTree,
6247 ReductionData.getKind());
6248 VectorizedTree =
6249 VectReductionData.createOp(Builder, "op.rdx", ReductionOps);
6250 } else
6251 VectorizedTree = ReducedSubTree;
6252 i += ReduxWidth;
6253 ReduxWidth = PowerOf2Floor(NumReducedVals - i);
6254 }
6255
6256 if (VectorizedTree) {
6257 // Finish the reduction.
6258 for (; i < NumReducedVals; ++i) {
6259 auto *I = cast<Instruction>(ReducedVals[i]);
6260 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(I->getDebugLoc());
6261 OperationData VectReductionData(ReductionData.getOpcode(),
6262 VectorizedTree, I,
6263 ReductionData.getKind());
6264 VectorizedTree = VectReductionData.createOp(Builder, "", ReductionOps);
6265 }
6266 for (auto &Pair : ExternallyUsedValues) {
6267 // Add each externally used value to the final reduction.
6268 for (auto *I : Pair.second) {
6269 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(I->getDebugLoc());
6270 OperationData VectReductionData(ReductionData.getOpcode(),
6271 VectorizedTree, Pair.first,
6272 ReductionData.getKind());
6273 VectorizedTree = VectReductionData.createOp(Builder, "op.extra", I);
6274 }
6275 }
6276 // Update users.
6277 ReductionRoot->replaceAllUsesWith(VectorizedTree);
6278 }
6279 return VectorizedTree != nullptr;
6280 }
6281
6282 unsigned numReductionValues() const {
6283 return ReducedVals.size();
6284 }
6285
6286private:
6287 /// Calculate the cost of a reduction.
6288 int getReductionCost(TargetTransformInfo *TTI, Value *FirstReducedVal,
6289 unsigned ReduxWidth) {
6290 Type *ScalarTy = FirstReducedVal->getType();
6291 Type *VecTy = VectorType::get(ScalarTy, ReduxWidth);
6292
6293 int PairwiseRdxCost;
6294 int SplittingRdxCost;
6295 switch (ReductionData.getKind()) {
6296 case RK_Arithmetic:
6297 PairwiseRdxCost =
6298 TTI->getArithmeticReductionCost(ReductionData.getOpcode(), VecTy,
6299 /*IsPairwiseForm=*/true);
6300 SplittingRdxCost =
6301 TTI->getArithmeticReductionCost(ReductionData.getOpcode(), VecTy,
6302 /*IsPairwiseForm=*/false);
6303 break;
6304 case RK_Min:
6305 case RK_Max:
6306 case RK_UMin:
6307 case RK_UMax: {
6308 Type *VecCondTy = CmpInst::makeCmpResultType(VecTy);
6309 bool IsUnsigned = ReductionData.getKind() == RK_UMin ||
6310 ReductionData.getKind() == RK_UMax;
6311 PairwiseRdxCost =
6312 TTI->getMinMaxReductionCost(VecTy, VecCondTy,
6313 /*IsPairwiseForm=*/true, IsUnsigned);
6314 SplittingRdxCost =
6315 TTI->getMinMaxReductionCost(VecTy, VecCondTy,
6316 /*IsPairwiseForm=*/false, IsUnsigned);
6317 break;
6318 }
6319 case RK_None:
6320 llvm_unreachable("Expected arithmetic or min/max reduction operation");
6321 }
6322
6323 IsPairwiseReduction = PairwiseRdxCost < SplittingRdxCost;
6324 int VecReduxCost = IsPairwiseReduction ? PairwiseRdxCost : SplittingRdxCost;
6325
6326 int ScalarReduxCost;
6327 switch (ReductionData.getKind()) {
6328 case RK_Arithmetic:
6329 ScalarReduxCost =
6330 TTI->getArithmeticInstrCost(ReductionData.getOpcode(), ScalarTy);
6331 break;
6332 case RK_Min:
6333 case RK_Max:
6334 case RK_UMin:
6335 case RK_UMax:
6336 ScalarReduxCost =
6337 TTI->getCmpSelInstrCost(ReductionData.getOpcode(), ScalarTy) +
6338 TTI->getCmpSelInstrCost(Instruction::Select, ScalarTy,
6339 CmpInst::makeCmpResultType(ScalarTy));
6340 break;
6341 case RK_None:
6342 llvm_unreachable("Expected arithmetic or min/max reduction operation");
6343 }
6344 ScalarReduxCost *= (ReduxWidth - 1);
6345
6346 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Adding cost " << VecReduxCost - ScalarReduxCost
6347 << " for reduction that starts with " << *FirstReducedVal
6348 << " (It is a "
6349 << (IsPairwiseReduction ? "pairwise" : "splitting")
6350 << " reduction)\n");
6351
6352 return VecReduxCost - ScalarReduxCost;
6353 }
6354
6355 /// Emit a horizontal reduction of the vectorized value.
6356 Value *emitReduction(Value *VectorizedValue, IRBuilder<> &Builder,
6357 unsigned ReduxWidth, const TargetTransformInfo *TTI) {
6358 assert(VectorizedValue && "Need to have a vectorized tree node");
6359 assert(isPowerOf2_32(ReduxWidth) &&
6360 "We only handle power-of-two reductions for now");
6361
6362 if (!IsPairwiseReduction) {
6363 // FIXME: The builder should use an FMF guard. It should not be hard-coded
6364 // to 'fast'.
6365 assert(Builder.getFastMathFlags().isFast() && "Expected 'fast' FMF");
6366 return createSimpleTargetReduction(
6367 Builder, TTI, ReductionData.getOpcode(), VectorizedValue,
6368 ReductionData.getFlags(), ReductionOps.back());
6369 }
6370
6371 Value *TmpVec = VectorizedValue;
6372 for (unsigned i = ReduxWidth / 2; i != 0; i >>= 1) {
6373 Value *LeftMask =
6374 createRdxShuffleMask(ReduxWidth, i, true, true, Builder);
6375 Value *RightMask =
6376 createRdxShuffleMask(ReduxWidth, i, true, false, Builder);
6377
6378 Value *LeftShuf = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(
6379 TmpVec, UndefValue::get(TmpVec->getType()), LeftMask, "rdx.shuf.l");
6380 Value *RightShuf = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(
6381 TmpVec, UndefValue::get(TmpVec->getType()), (RightMask),
6382 "rdx.shuf.r");
6383 OperationData VectReductionData(ReductionData.getOpcode(), LeftShuf,
6384 RightShuf, ReductionData.getKind());
6385 TmpVec = VectReductionData.createOp(Builder, "op.rdx", ReductionOps);
6386 }
6387
6388 // The result is in the first element of the vector.
6389 return Builder.CreateExtractElement(TmpVec, Builder.getInt32(0));
6390 }
6391};
6392
6393} // end anonymous namespace
6394
6395/// Recognize construction of vectors like
6396/// %ra = insertelement <4 x float> undef, float %s0, i32 0
6397/// %rb = insertelement <4 x float> %ra, float %s1, i32 1
6398/// %rc = insertelement <4 x float> %rb, float %s2, i32 2
6399/// %rd = insertelement <4 x float> %rc, float %s3, i32 3
6400/// starting from the last insertelement instruction.
6401///
6402/// Returns true if it matches
6403static bool findBuildVector(InsertElementInst *LastInsertElem,
6404 TargetTransformInfo *TTI,
6405 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &BuildVectorOpds,
6406 int &UserCost) {
6407 UserCost = 0;
6408 Value *V = nullptr;
6409 do {
6410 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(LastInsertElem->getOperand(2))) {
6411 UserCost += TTI->getVectorInstrCost(Instruction::InsertElement,
6412 LastInsertElem->getType(),
6413 CI->getZExtValue());
6414 }
6415 BuildVectorOpds.push_back(LastInsertElem->getOperand(1));
6416 V = LastInsertElem->getOperand(0);
6417 if (isa<UndefValue>(V))
6418 break;
6419 LastInsertElem = dyn_cast<InsertElementInst>(V);
6420 if (!LastInsertElem || !LastInsertElem->hasOneUse())
6421 return false;
6422 } while (true);
6423 std::reverse(BuildVectorOpds.begin(), BuildVectorOpds.end());
6424 return true;
6425}
6426
6427/// Like findBuildVector, but looks for construction of aggregate.
6428///
6429/// \return true if it matches.
6430static bool findBuildAggregate(InsertValueInst *IV,
6431 SmallVectorImpl<Value *> &BuildVectorOpds) {
6432 Value *V;
6433 do {
6434 BuildVectorOpds.push_back(IV->getInsertedValueOperand());
6435 V = IV->getAggregateOperand();
6436 if (isa<UndefValue>(V))
6437 break;
6438 IV = dyn_cast<InsertValueInst>(V);
6439 if (!IV || !IV->hasOneUse())
6440 return false;
6441 } while (true);
6442 std::reverse(BuildVectorOpds.begin(), BuildVectorOpds.end());
6443 return true;
6444}
6445
6446static bool PhiTypeSorterFunc(Value *V, Value *V2) {
6447 return V->getType() < V2->getType();
6448}
6449
6450/// Try and get a reduction value from a phi node.
6451///
6452/// Given a phi node \p P in a block \p ParentBB, consider possible reductions
6453/// if they come from either \p ParentBB or a containing loop latch.
6454///
6455/// \returns A candidate reduction value if possible, or \code nullptr \endcode
6456/// if not possible.
6457static Value *getReductionValue(const DominatorTree *DT, PHINode *P,
6458 BasicBlock *ParentBB, LoopInfo *LI) {
6459 // There are situations where the reduction value is not dominated by the
6460 // reduction phi. Vectorizing such cases has been reported to cause
6461 // miscompiles. See PR25787.
6462 auto DominatedReduxValue = [&](Value *R) {
6463 return isa<Instruction>(R) &&
6464 DT->dominates(P->getParent(), cast<Instruction>(R)->getParent());
6465 };
6466
6467 Value *Rdx = nullptr;
6468
6469 // Return the incoming value if it comes from the same BB as the phi node.
6470 if (P->getIncomingBlock(0) == ParentBB) {
6471 Rdx = P->getIncomingValue(0);
6472 } else if (P->getIncomingBlock(1) == ParentBB) {
6473 Rdx = P->getIncomingValue(1);
6474 }
6475
6476 if (Rdx && DominatedReduxValue(Rdx))
6477 return Rdx;
6478
6479 // Otherwise, check whether we have a loop latch to look at.
6480 Loop *BBL = LI->getLoopFor(ParentBB);
6481 if (!BBL)
6482 return nullptr;
6483 BasicBlock *BBLatch = BBL->getLoopLatch();
6484 if (!BBLatch)
6485 return nullptr;
6486
6487 // There is a loop latch, return the incoming value if it comes from
6488 // that. This reduction pattern occasionally turns up.
6489 if (P->getIncomingBlock(0) == BBLatch) {
6490 Rdx = P->getIncomingValue(0);
6491 } else if (P->getIncomingBlock(1) == BBLatch) {
6492 Rdx = P->getIncomingValue(1);
6493 }
6494
6495 if (Rdx && DominatedReduxValue(Rdx))
6496 return Rdx;
6497
6498 return nullptr;
6499}
6500
6501/// Attempt to reduce a horizontal reduction.
6502/// If it is legal to match a horizontal reduction feeding the phi node \a P
6503/// with reduction operators \a Root (or one of its operands) in a basic block
6504/// \a BB, then check if it can be done. If horizontal reduction is not found
6505/// and root instruction is a binary operation, vectorization of the operands is
6506/// attempted.
6507/// \returns true if a horizontal reduction was matched and reduced or operands
6508/// of one of the binary instruction were vectorized.
6509/// \returns false if a horizontal reduction was not matched (or not possible)
6510/// or no vectorization of any binary operation feeding \a Root instruction was
6511/// performed.
6512static bool tryToVectorizeHorReductionOrInstOperands(
6513 PHINode *P, Instruction *Root, BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R,
6514 TargetTransformInfo *TTI,
6515 const function_ref<bool(Instruction *, BoUpSLP &)> Vectorize) {
6516 if (!ShouldVectorizeHor)
6517 return false;
6518
6519 if (!Root)
6520 return false;
6521
6522 if (Root->getParent() != BB || isa<PHINode>(Root))
6523 return false;
6524 // Start analysis starting from Root instruction. If horizontal reduction is
6525 // found, try to vectorize it. If it is not a horizontal reduction or
6526 // vectorization is not possible or not effective, and currently analyzed
6527 // instruction is a binary operation, try to vectorize the operands, using
6528 // pre-order DFS traversal order. If the operands were not vectorized, repeat
6529 // the same procedure considering each operand as a possible root of the
6530 // horizontal reduction.
6531 // Interrupt the process if the Root instruction itself was vectorized or all
6532 // sub-trees not higher that RecursionMaxDepth were analyzed/vectorized.
6533 SmallVector<std::pair<WeakTrackingVH, unsigned>, 8> Stack(1, {Root, 0});
6534 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 8> VisitedInstrs;
6535 bool Res = false;
6536 while (!Stack.empty()) {
6537 Value *V;
6538 unsigned Level;
6539 std::tie(V, Level) = Stack.pop_back_val();
6540 if (!V)
6541 continue;
6542 auto *Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
6543 if (!Inst)
6544 continue;
6545 auto *BI = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Inst);
6546 auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(Inst);
6547 if (BI || SI) {
6548 HorizontalReduction HorRdx;
6549 if (HorRdx.matchAssociativeReduction(P, Inst)) {
6550 if (HorRdx.tryToReduce(R, TTI)) {
6551 Res = true;
6552 // Set P to nullptr to avoid re-analysis of phi node in
6553 // matchAssociativeReduction function unless this is the root node.
6554 P = nullptr;
6555 continue;
6556 }
6557 }
6558 if (P && BI) {
6559 Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(BI->getOperand(0));
6560 if (Inst == P)
6561 Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(BI->getOperand(1));
6562 if (!Inst) {
6563 // Set P to nullptr to avoid re-analysis of phi node in
6564 // matchAssociativeReduction function unless this is the root node.
6565 P = nullptr;
6566 continue;
6567 }
6568 }
6569 }
6570 // Set P to nullptr to avoid re-analysis of phi node in
6571 // matchAssociativeReduction function unless this is the root node.
6572 P = nullptr;
6573 if (Vectorize(Inst, R)) {
6574 Res = true;
6575 continue;
6576 }
6577
6578 // Try to vectorize operands.
6579 // Continue analysis for the instruction from the same basic block only to
6580 // save compile time.
6581 if (++Level < RecursionMaxDepth)
6582 for (auto *Op : Inst->operand_values())
6583 if (VisitedInstrs.insert(Op).second)
6584 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Op))
6585 if (!isa<PHINode>(I) && I->getParent() == BB)
6586 Stack.emplace_back(Op, Level);
6587 }
6588 return Res;
6589}
6590
6591bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeRootInstruction(PHINode *P, Value *V,
6592 BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R,
6593 TargetTransformInfo *TTI) {
6594 if (!V)
6595 return false;
6596 auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V);
6597 if (!I)
6598 return false;
6599
6600 if (!isa<BinaryOperator>(I))
6601 P = nullptr;
6602 // Try to match and vectorize a horizontal reduction.
6603 auto &&ExtraVectorization = [this](Instruction *I, BoUpSLP &R) -> bool {
6604 return tryToVectorize(I, R);
6605 };
6606 return tryToVectorizeHorReductionOrInstOperands(P, I, BB, R, TTI,
6607 ExtraVectorization);
6608}
6609
6610bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeInsertValueInst(InsertValueInst *IVI,
6611 BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R) {
6612 const DataLayout &DL = BB->getModule()->getDataLayout();
6613 if (!R.canMapToVector(IVI->getType(), DL))
6614 return false;
6615
6616 SmallVector<Value *, 16> BuildVectorOpds;
6617 if (!findBuildAggregate(IVI, BuildVectorOpds))
6618 return false;
6619
6620 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: array mappable to vector: " << *IVI << "\n");
6621 // Aggregate value is unlikely to be processed in vector register, we need to
6622 // extract scalars into scalar registers, so NeedExtraction is set true.
6623 return tryToVectorizeList(BuildVectorOpds, R);
6624}
6625
6626bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeInsertElementInst(InsertElementInst *IEI,
6627 BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R) {
6628 int UserCost;
6629 SmallVector<Value *, 16> BuildVectorOpds;
6630 if (!findBuildVector(IEI, TTI, BuildVectorOpds, UserCost) ||
6631 (llvm::all_of(BuildVectorOpds,
6632 [](Value *V) { return isa<ExtractElementInst>(V); }) &&
6633 isShuffle(BuildVectorOpds)))
6634 return false;
6635
6636 // Vectorize starting with the build vector operands ignoring the BuildVector
6637 // instructions for the purpose of scheduling and user extraction.
6638 return tryToVectorizeList(BuildVectorOpds, R, UserCost);
6639}
6640
6641bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeCmpInst(CmpInst *CI, BasicBlock *BB,
6642 BoUpSLP &R) {
6643 if (tryToVectorizePair(CI->getOperand(0), CI->getOperand(1), R))
6644 return true;
6645
6646 bool OpsChanged = false;
6647 for (int Idx = 0; Idx < 2; ++Idx) {
6648 OpsChanged |=
6649 vectorizeRootInstruction(nullptr, CI->getOperand(Idx), BB, R, TTI);
6650 }
6651 return OpsChanged;
6652}
6653
6654bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeSimpleInstructions(
6655 SmallVectorImpl<WeakVH> &Instructions, BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R) {
6656 bool OpsChanged = false;
6657 for (auto &VH : reverse(Instructions)) {
6658 auto *I = dyn_cast_or_null<Instruction>(VH);
6659 if (!I)
6660 continue;
6661 if (auto *LastInsertValue = dyn_cast<InsertValueInst>(I))
6662 OpsChanged |= vectorizeInsertValueInst(LastInsertValue, BB, R);
6663 else if (auto *LastInsertElem = dyn_cast<InsertElementInst>(I))
6664 OpsChanged |= vectorizeInsertElementInst(LastInsertElem, BB, R);
6665 else if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(I))
6666 OpsChanged |= vectorizeCmpInst(CI, BB, R);
6667 }
6668 Instructions.clear();
6669 return OpsChanged;
6670}
6671
6672bool SLPVectorizerPass::vectorizeChainsInBlock(BasicBlock *BB, BoUpSLP &R) {
6673 bool Changed = false;
6674 SmallVector<Value *, 4> Incoming;
6675 SmallPtrSet<Value *, 16> VisitedInstrs;
6676
6677 bool HaveVectorizedPhiNodes = true;
6678 while (HaveVectorizedPhiNodes) {
6679 HaveVectorizedPhiNodes = false;
6680
6681 // Collect the incoming values from the PHIs.
6682 Incoming.clear();
6683 for (Instruction &I : *BB) {
6684 PHINode *P = dyn_cast<PHINode>(&I);
6685 if (!P)
6686 break;
6687
6688 if (!VisitedInstrs.count(P))
6689 Incoming.push_back(P);
6690 }
6691
6692 // Sort by type.
6693 llvm::stable_sort(Incoming, PhiTypeSorterFunc);
6694
6695 // Try to vectorize elements base on their type.
6696 for (SmallVector<Value *, 4>::iterator IncIt = Incoming.begin(),
6697 E = Incoming.end();
6698 IncIt != E;) {
6699
6700 // Look for the next elements with the same type.
6701 SmallVector<Value *, 4>::iterator SameTypeIt = IncIt;
6702 while (SameTypeIt != E &&
6703 (*SameTypeIt)->getType() == (*IncIt)->getType()) {
6704 VisitedInstrs.insert(*SameTypeIt);
6705 ++SameTypeIt;
6706 }
6707
6708 // Try to vectorize them.
6709 unsigned NumElts = (SameTypeIt - IncIt);
6710 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Trying to vectorize starting at PHIs ("
6711 << NumElts << ")\n");
6712 // The order in which the phi nodes appear in the program does not matter.
6713 // So allow tryToVectorizeList to reorder them if it is beneficial. This
6714 // is done when there are exactly two elements since tryToVectorizeList
6715 // asserts that there are only two values when AllowReorder is true.
6716 bool AllowReorder = NumElts == 2;
6717 if (NumElts > 1 && tryToVectorizeList(makeArrayRef(IncIt, NumElts), R,
6718 /*UserCost=*/0, AllowReorder)) {
6719 // Success start over because instructions might have been changed.
6720 HaveVectorizedPhiNodes = true;
6721 Changed = true;
